{
  "texts": [
    "Since D 2 is a constant (D 2 = 55000), both the calculated similarity x 2i and the difference R i between x 2i and y 2i for each sentence pair are constants.",
    "The constraint function is revised as R i0 = λ 2 y 2i, where |R i | = |x 2iy 2i | represents the absolute value of semantic deviation.",
    "When λ 2 increases, |R i0 | also increases, indicating that the sentence pairs that need to be recalculated will no longer satisfy the constraint function.",
    "Take all sentence pairs with y 2i = 0.5 as an example to explain.",
    "When λ 2 = 0.1, |R i0 | = 0.1 × 0.5 = 0.05, which means that sentence pairs with calculated sentence similarity x i falling outside the range I 1 = [0.45, 0.55] need to be optimized using WQE."
  ]
}